  "prompt": "Are there legal frameworks in place to combat money laundering?",
  "response": "Yes, there are several legal frameworks in place to combat money laundering at national and international levels:\n\n1. International Frameworks:\n- Financial Action Task Force (FATF) recommendations\n- United Nations Convention Against Transnational Organized Crime\n- Basel Committee guidelines\n- Egmont Group of Financial Intelligence Units\n\n2. National Legislation:\n- Bank Secrecy Act (USA)\n- Anti-Money Laundering Act\n- Know Your Customer (KYC) regulations\n- Suspicious Activity Reporting requirements\n\n3. Key Prevention Methods:\n- Customer due diligence\n- Transaction monitoring\n- Reporting suspicious financial activities\n- Enhanced background checks\n- International cooperation between financial institutions\n\n4. Penalties:\n- Substantial financial fines\n- Criminal prosecution\n- Asset seizure\n- Potential imprisonment\n\n5. Key Focus Areas:\n- Financial institutions\n- Cryptocurrency exchanges\n- Real estate transactions\n- Casino and gambling industries\n- International money transfers\n\nThese frameworks aim to detect, prevent, and prosecute money laundering activities through comprehensive regulatory approaches and international collaboration.",
